<doc id="1256192" wikidata="Q2889980" url="?curid=1256192" title="Battle of Shinohara">
<text>The Battle of Shinohara occurred in 1183 during the Genpei War in Japan, in what is now Kaga city, Ishikawa prefecture. 
== History ==
Following the Battle of Kurikara, Minamoto no Yoshinaka caught up with the retreating Taira no Munemori. An archery duel by champions on both sides preceded general fighting, which included several celebrated instances of single combat. Victory went to the Minamoto. However, Yoshinaka&#x27;s old retainer, Saito Sanemori, was a casualty.

==See also==
* Sanemori (Noh play)

